// Cortex-M3 + 64 KB SRAM / 512 KB flash, plus a RAM-mapped DAC register window for
// the thin-seam software-triggered DAC driver content-gate. The gate asserts the
// exact register effects the DRIVER writes — CR enable word (0x3D), DHR staged code,
// SWTRIGR trigger bit — and the Kani-proven glitch-free property (DHR write does NOT
// move DOR until a trigger), on a plain memory region, deterministic, no dependence
// on Renode's DAC peripheral model.
cpu: CPU.CortexM @ sysbus
    cpuType: "cortex-m3"
    nvic: nvic
nvic: IRQControllers.NVIC @ sysbus 0xE000E000
    -> cpu@0
flash: Memory.MappedMemory @ sysbus 0x0
    size: 0x80000
sram: Memory.MappedMemory @ sysbus 0x20000000
    size: 0x10000
// DAC register window (real STM32F1 address, 0x40007400) as plain memory — driver
// CR/DHR/SWTRIGR/DOR writes read back. Ends at 0x40007800, below USART1 at 0x40013800
// (no overlap).
dac: Memory.MappedMemory @ sysbus 0x40007400
    size: 0x400
usart1: UART.STM32_UART @ sysbus <0x40013800, +0x100>
    -> nvic@37
